A 'Libellula quadrimaculata' is a species of dragonfly.
It has a bright metallic green body and large transparent wings.
Its wingspan can reach up to 80mm.
The hindwings have a distinctive black spot near the base.
The eyes are large and rounded, and the legs are long and slender.
It can be found in open habitats near water sources such as ponds and streams.
The 'Libellula quadrimaculata' feeds on small insects and is an important predator in aquatic ecosystems.
